article.headline: Drake 59, Texas-Pan American 57
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Josh Young's jumper with three seconds left gave Drake a 59-57 win over Texas-Pan American on Friday. The Bulldogs (7-2) scored the last eight points of the game after trailing 57-51 with 2:34 to play. Nick Weiermiller missed a 3-pointer as time ran out for the Broncs (2-6). Young, who finished with 7 points, had a 3-pointer with 1:43 to play to bring the Bulldogs within 57-55 and Craig Stanley tied it with a minute to play. The Broncs then missed two straight shots before Young's game-winner. Josh Parker led Drake with 18 points and Stanley added 10. Texas-Pan American got 21 points from Ben Smith. He was the only Bronc player in double figures.
